race.comment: MOUNT BONA (6) is back from a spell and closed last prep with a 1.2L defeat over 1500m at Newcastle. She was a big Maiden winner here two back and Bullock strikes at a whopping 41% with the smart local yard. Should be ready to go and will be naturally improved. LAIZABOUT (2) raced on the speed when resuming over 1300m at Dubbo and found one better. He's also back in grade and has a low gate and handy 1.5kg claim. In the right race and is a key runner. MONEY GAMES (9) is sure to build on his Tamworth Maiden win on debut. There was plenty of merit in that effort but he may have to do it the hard way again. CHESTIME (8) won a 50 comfortably at Gunnedah. Didn't have much luck in a CL2 here first up and fitter also has claims.
